            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EThis%20verse%20contains%20both%20a%20promise%20and%20a%20penalty.%20The%20encouraging%20part%20of%20the%20scripture%20is%20that%20God%20is%20looking%20for%20just%20one%20person%20who%20will%20be%20righteous%20and%20pray%20fervently%20for%20his%20nation.%20We%20sometimes%20wait%20for%20crowds%20and%20multitudes%20to%20join%20us%20in%20prayer%2C%20but%20God%20is%20looking%20for%20even%20one%20individual%20who%20will%20intercede%20for%20his%20country.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThat%20one%20person%20must%20see%20himself%20as%20mediating%20a%20large%20gap%20between%20a%20holy%20God%20and%20a%20sinful%20nation%20destined%20for%20His%20judgment.%20What%20an%20important%20position!%20Because%20Moses%20willingly%20stood%20in%20such%20a%20gap%2C%20the%20nation%20of%20Israel%20was%20spared.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20sad%20reality%20of%20the%20situation%20in%20Ezekiel%20was%20that%20even%20though%20God%20needed%20only%20one%20person%2C%20He%20could%20not%20find%20a%20single%20one.%20Today%20may%20you%20and%20I%20be%20such%20an%20intercessor%2C%20knowing%20our%20rights%20in%20the%20new%20covenant%20of%20grace.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EAlways%20remember%3A%20You%20may%20be%20that%20person%20upon%20whom%20God%20is%20focused-the%20one%20who%20is%20holding%20back%20His%20wrath.%20Keep%20praying%2C%20for%20God%20is%20surely%20watching!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
